rance%20rover%20to%20Mars'%20surface%20in%202021.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FJPL-Caltech%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20option%20involves%20working%20with%20existing%20commercial%20partners%2C%20like%20SpaceX%20and%20Blue%20Origin.%20In%20that%20scenario%2C%20NASA%20would%20use%20new%20commercial%20technology%2C%20untested%20on%20Mars%2C%20like%20a%20heavy%20lander%2C%20Nelson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20paths%20would%20cost%20around%20%246%20or%20%247%20billion%20and%20deliver%20the%20samples%20to%20Earth%20before%202040%2C%20NASA%20determined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENelson%20said%20he%20expects%20NASA%20to%20choose%20one%20of%20those%20paths%20forward%20in%202026%20since%20the%20engineering%20work%20required%20to%20fully%20understand%20each%20option%20will%20take%20about%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20NASA%20will%20need%20%24300%20million%20to%20do%20that%20work%20in%20fiscal%20year%202025.%20Trump%20would%20have%20to%20include%20that%20expense%20in%20his%20budget%20proposal%2C%20and%20Congress%20would%20have%20to%20approve%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20they%20want%20to%20get%20this%20thing%20back%20on%20a%20direct%20return%20earlier%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20put%20more%20money%20into%20it%2C%20even%20more%20than%20%24300%20million%20in%20fiscal%20year%2025.%20And%20that%20would%20be%20the%20case%20every%20year%20going%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Nelson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20transition%20to%20the%20new%20Trump%20administration%2C%20Nelson%20will%20likely%20be%20handing%20the%20agency%20over%20to%20Trump-nominee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-tech-billionaire-astronaut-jared-isaacman-future-missions-uncertain-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJared%20Isaacman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20billionaire%20and%20two-time%20SpaceX%20astronaut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Trump%20nominated%20him%20for%20NASA%20Administrator%2C%20Isaacman%20wrote%20in%20a%2