nd%20same-sex%20marriage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20sat%20down%20for%20a%20wide-ranging%20interview%20with%20NDTV%20in%20which%20he%20spoke%20about%20everything%20from%20how%20he%20almost%20became%20an%20economist%20and%20the%20paltry%20fees%20he%20got%20for%20his%20first%20case%20to%20the%20criticisms%20levelled%20against%20judges%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandrachud%20also%20addressed%20a%20colleague's%20remarks%20of%20him%20being%20harsh%20on%20a%20former%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20spoke%20about%20the%20need%20for%20revisiting%20and%20overturning%20earlier%20judgments%20-%20even%20those%20by%20his%20father%20and%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20Chief%20Justice%20YV%20Chandrachud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEarly%20Days%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20question%20about%20his%20experiences%20and%20what%20he%20learnt%20from%20his%20father%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%20his%20first%20choice%20was%20to%20pursue%20a%20post-graduate%20degree%20in%20Economics.%20Later%2C%20when%20it%20seemed%20like%20he%20would%20remain%20a%20lawyer%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life%2C%20his%20father%20told%20him%20he%20would%20support%20him%20no%20matter%20what%20he%20did.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLaw%20was%20not%20my%20first%20choice%2C%20to%20be%20very%20honest.%20I%20graduated%20from%20St%20Stephen's%20College%20in%20Economics%20and%20Mathematics.%20And%2C%20after%20I%20completed%20my%20BA%2C%20my%20first%20choice%20was%20actually%20to%20pursue%20a%20Post-Graduation%20in%20Economics%20at%20the%20Delhi%20School%20of%20Economics.%20But%2C%20as%20destiny%20would%20have%20it%2C%20I%20joined%20the%20law%20faculty%20and%20then%20there%20was%20no%20going%20back.%20My%20father%2C%20of%20course%2C%20was%20a%20very%20important%20source%20of%20influence%20on%20my%20life%2C%20not%20just%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20law%2C%20but%20in%20terms%20of%20learning%20basic%20values%2C%20the%20ethical%20values%2C%20which%20are%20associated%20with%20life.%20That%20generation%20of%20judges%20and%20lawyers%20was%20very%20strong%20in%20their%20foundational%20principles%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStressing%20that%20his%20father%20made%20time%20for%20his%20family%20and%20never%20imposed%20his%20view%20on%20them%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%20he%20also%20left%20it%20up%20to%20him%20to%20choose%20his%20career%20path.%20In%20their%20later%20years%2C%20he%20said%2C%20his%20father%20was%20more%20of%20a%20friend%20to%20him%2C%20and%20that%20friendship%20continued%20till%20the%20end.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20when%20the%20call%20of%20higher%20judicial%20office%20came%20to%20me%20-%20I%20was%20asked%20to%20become%20a%20judge%20when%20I%20was%20just%2038%20years%20old%20-%20and%20my%20appointment%20was%20not%20coming%20through%20for%20two%20years%2C%20I%20thought%2C%20well%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20get%20on%20with%20the%20law%20and%20be%20a%20lawyer%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20life.%20And%20when%20I%20looked%20at%20him%20(my%20father)%20for%20advice%2C%20he%20said%2C%20do%20as%20you%20please%2C%20and%20I'll%20support%20you%20in%20whatever%20you%20do.%20Perhaps%2C%20he%20said%2C%20you%20will%20do%20equally%20satisfying%20work%20and%20fulfilling%20law%20work%20as%20a%20lawyer%20at%20the%20bar%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20also%20said%20he%20had%20the%20good%20fortune%20of%20belonging%20to%20a%20generation%20when%20some%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bgreats%20of%20the%20bar%26quot%3B%20were%20still%20active.%20He%20said%20he%20learnt%20immensely%20from%20Fali%20Nariman%2C%20Soli%20Sorabjee%20and%20K%20Parasaran.%20He%20also%20praised%20former%20Solicitor%20General%20KK%20Venugopal%2C%20calling%20him%20%26quot%3Bextraordinarily%20brilliant%26quot%3B%20in%20both%20commercial%20and%20constitutional%20cases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirst%20Fee%20After%20Harvard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandrachud%20said%20he%20learnt%20a%20policy%20oriented%20approach%20to%20law%20at%20Harvard%20Law%20School%20and%20also%20got%20educated%20in%20policy%20as%20a%20student%20of%20Economics%20at%20Delhi%20University%20and%20at%20the%20Campus%20Law%20Centre%20in%20Delhi.%20Professor%20Lotika%20Sarkar%2C%20he%20said%2C%20gave%20students%20like%20him%20the%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20groundings%26quot%3B%20in%20feminist%20jurisprudence%20when%20people%20were%20not%20talking%20about%20feminism%20in%20law%20in%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Harvard%20Law%20degree%20did%20not%2C%20however%2C%20have%20much%20of%20an%20impact%20immediately%20after%20he%20returned%20to%20practice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20realised%20this%20to%20my%20disappointment%20when%20I%20got%20my%20first%20brief%20as%20a%20young%20lawyer%20in%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court.%20I%20had%20an%20SJD%20from%20Harvard%20Law%20School%2C%20which%20is%20a%20Doctorate%20in%20Juridical%20Science%2C%20and%20my%20first%20brief%20was%20a%20little%20docket%20to%20mention%20before%20a%20division%20bench%20of%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court.%20I%20asked%20the%20solicitor%3A%20'How%20much%20do%20I%20mark%20on%20the%20docket%2C%20what%20is%20my%20fee%3F'%26quot%3B%20he%20recounted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFees%20in%20Bombay%20in%20those%20days%20were%20marked%20in%20GMs%2C%20which%20is%20gold%20mohurs%2C%20and%20one%20GM%20was%2015%20rupees.%20So%20the%20solicitor%20looked%20at%20me%20and%20said%2C%20'You%20know%2C%20for%20this%20particular%20work%2C%20the%20ordinary%20fee%20would%20be%20five%20GMs%2C%20which%20would%20be%2075%20rupees.%20But%20since%20you%20are%20first%20appearing%20before%20the%20high%20court%2C%20I%20will%20give%20you%20six%20guineas%20for%20this%20case.'%20So%20I%20realised%20that%2C%20notwithstanding%20a%20Harvard%20PhD%2C%20what%20I%20could%20mark%20in%20those%20days%20was%20about%2075%20rupees%20or%2090%20rupees%20in%20the%20mid-eighties%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20life%20teaches%20you%20so%20many%20good%20lessons%2C%20you%20know%3F%20And%20you%20realise%20that%20a%20good%20academic%20degree%20is%20important%2C%20but%20it%20is%20not%20everything%20in%20itself%20when%20you%20actually%20join%20the%20profession.%20But%20Harvard%20benefited%20me%20as%20time%20went%20on...%20When%20I%20became%20a%20judge%20and%20started%20writing%20about%20the%20law%20and%20not%20just%20speaking%20about%20the%20law%2C%20I%20realised%20what%20an%20imperceptible%20impact%20Harvard%20had%20on%20my%20way%20of%20thought%20as%20an%20individual.%20So%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20are%20not%20so%20perceptible%20when%20you%20first%20join%20the%20profession%2C%20but%20the%20impact%20of%20what%20you've%20learned%20emerges%20later%20on%20in%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EElectoral%20Bonds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20said%20that%20when%20he%20was%20a%20judge%20at%20the%20High%20Court%2C%20there%20was%20comfort%20in%20knowing%20that%20there%20was%20a%20higher%20court%20that%20could%20correct%20any%20inadvertent%20errors.%20That%20was%20not%20the%20case%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20that%20was%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20no%20case%20in%20the%20top%20court%20was%20ever%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20speaks%2C%20it%20speaks%20for%20the%20present%2C%20and%20it%20speaks%20for%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20one%20of%20his%20most%20important%20judgments%2C%20the%20scrapping%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20as%20a%20method%20of%20political%20funding%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%20a%20judge%20is%20aware%20of%20the%20ramifications%20of%20the%20judgment%20but%20applies%20intellectual%20rigour%20and%20the%20basic%20principles%20of%20law%20to%20arrive%20at%20a%20verdict.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20instance%2C%20when%20you%20decide%20a%20case%20like%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case%2C%20when%20it%20opens%2C%20you%20are%20conscious%20of%20the%20ramifications%20of%20what%20you%20are%20deciding%20and%20you%20are%20conscious%20of%20the%20impact%20which%20the%20case%20will%20have%20on%20the%20polity%20in%20the%20long%20run%20-%20it%20is%20obviously%20something%20which%20is%20present%20to%20the%20mind%20of%20the%20court.%20But%20when%20you%20are%20deciding%20the%20case%20in%20terms%20of%20intellectual%20rigour%2C%20you%20are%20applying%20the%20basic%20principles%20which%20are%20associated%20with%20that%20body%20of%20law.%20So%2C%20in%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case%2C%20we%20were%20applying%20fundamental%20principles%20of%20manifest%20arbitrariness%20or%20the%20need%20for%20transparency%20in%20electoral%20funding%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20principles%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%2C%20have%20been%20developed%20over%20decades%20and%20judges%20are%20conscious%20that%20what%20they%20are%20deciding%20now%20will%20impact%20society%20in%20the%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20constantly%20reminds%20you%2C%20as%20a%20judge%2C%20to%20be%20humble.%20Humility%20is%20something%20you%20learn%20as%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20because%20you%20are%20conscious%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20field%20of%20knowledge%20is%20so%20vast%2C%20and%20it's%20far%20vaster%20than%20any%20of%20us%20as%20judges%20or%20lawyers%20can%20fathom%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20also%20highlighted%20how%20judging%20can%20be%20a%20very%20lonely%20task.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20arguments%20close%2C%20that's%20the%20time%20for%20reflection%20for%20a%20judge.%20When%20a%20case%20is%20concluded%20in%20terms%20of%20arguments%20and%20you%20reserve%20a%20case%20for%20judgment%2C%20that's%20when%20the%20real%20process%20of%20judging%20starts%20because%20then%20you%20are%20just%20left%20to%20yourself.%20There%20is%20no%20one%20else%20with%20you%20but%20your%20papers.%20And%2C%20in%20our%20case%20now%2C%20this%20is%20a%20digital%20format%2C%20so%20the%20digitised%20files%20and%20yourself.%20So%2C%20in%20that%20sense%2C%20judging%20itself%20is%20a%20very%20lonely%20task%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOverturning%20Father's%20Judgments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20a%20question%20on%20a%20former%20top%20court%20judge%20saying%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20%26quot%3Bsupreme%20but%20not%20infallible%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20former%20chief%20justice%20summed%20up%20his%20thoughts%20succinctly%2C%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20final%20not%20because%20it%20is%20right%2C%20but%20it%20is%20right%20because%20it%20is%20final.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20he%20explained%2C%20was%20the%20reason%20why%20some%20past%20judgments%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20were%20relooked%20at%20and%20overruled%2C%20including%20in%202024%2C%20when%20he%20retired%20as%20the%20Chief%20Justice.%20The%20former%20judge%20said%20this%20did%20not%20necessarily%20mean%20that%20the%20judgments%20were%20wrong%20-%20they%20may%20have%20been%20right%20in%20their%20context%20but%20may%20not%20make%20sense%20in%20today's%20society.%20It%20was%20this%2C%20he%20said%2C%20that%20led%20to%20him%20overruling%20two%20judgments%20delivered%20by%20his%20father.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20instance%2C%20you%20know%2C%20there%20was%20a%20judgment%20of%20Justice%20Krishna%20Iyer%20on%20property%2C%20which%20we%20recently%20had%20a%20look%20at%20again.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20said%20that%20because%20the%20individual%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20community%2C%20every%20property%20which%20belongs%20to%20the%20individual%20is%20property%20of%20the%20community%20in%20the%20context%20of%20Article%2039%20(b)%20and%20(c).%20%C2%A0Now%2C%20this%20judgment%20was%20delivered%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20society%20when%20it%20was%20delivered%20-%20a%20very%20tightly%20regulated%20economy%2C%20central%20planning.%20All%20that%20changed%20after%201990%2C%20when%20the%20market%20reforms%20took%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BBetween%201990%20and%202024%2C%20India%20has%20evolved%20as%20a%20society%2C%20as%20an%20economy.%20So%2C%20%C2%A0intrinsic%20to%20the%20work%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20relook%20at%20the%20judgments%20of%20the%20past.%20And%2C%20in%20that%20process%2C%20I%20overruled%20a%20couple%20of%20judgments%20delivered%20by%20my%20own%20father.%20But%20that's%20part%20of%20the%20judicial%20process.%20Incidentally%2C%20they%20happen%20to%20be%20judgments%20of%20my%20father%2C%20but%20I%20would%20have%20done%20that%20anyway%20as%20part%20of%20our%20constitutional%20duty.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmergency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20remarks%20by%20a%20colleague%20that%20he%20had%20been%20unduly%20harsh%20to%20a%20former%20judge%2C%20the%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20explained%20that%20some%20of%20what%20was%20attributed%20to%20him%20was%20not%20in%20the%20judgment%20and%20could%20have%20been%20in%20a%20draft%20circulated%20to%20other%20judges.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWell%2C%20for%20one%20thing%2C%20some%20of%20the%20words%20which%20are%20attributed%20to%20me%20as%20having%20been%20actually%20said%20in%20the%20judgment%20are%20not%20in%20the%20judgment%2C%20for%20the%20reason%20that%20maybe%20those%20observations%20were%20there%20in%20a%20draft%20which%20was%20circulated%20to%20colleagues...%20And%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%20after%20a%20very%20well-meaning%20colleague%20requested%20me%20to%20look%20at%20that%20particular%20observation%2C%20I%20deleted%20it%20from%20the%20judgment.%20But%20how%20you%20phrase%20the%20judgment%20is%2C%20again%20a%20perception%20of%20that%20individual.%20And%20I%20don't%20believe%20that%20to%20say%20that%20a%20judgment%20is%20'wrong'%20or%20'terribly%20wrong'%20is%20harsh%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPointing%20to%20the%20ADM%20Jabalpur%20case%20during%20the%20Emergency%2C%20which%20dealt%20with%20the%20suspension%20of%20rights%20-%20a%20judgment%20to%20which%20his%20father%20was%20a%20party%20-%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%20strong%20statements%20were%20made%20when%20it%20was%20overruled%20because%20the%20judges%20felt%20strongly%20about%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20overruled%20that%20initially%20when%20we%20decided%20the%20Puttaswamy%20case%20where%20we%20decided%20the%20right%20to%20privacy.%20When%20we%20decided%20Puttaswamy%2C%20we%20said%20that%20the%20judgment%20was%20terribly%20wrong%20because%20the%20right%20to%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty%20does%20not%20originate%20in%20the%20Constitution.%20Even%20if%20there's%20no%20Constitution%2C%20human%20beings%20in%20a%20civilised%20society%2C%20in%20a%20democratic%20society%2C%20have%20the%20right%20to%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty.%20The%20Constitution%20recognised%20the%20right%20to%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty%2C%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20we%20overruled%20that%20judgment%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%2C%20while%20we%20overruled%20it%2C%20we%20were%20also%20conscious%20as%20judges%20of%20the%20excesses%20which%20took%20place%20in%20the%20course%20of%20the%20internal%20Emergency%20which%20was%20declared%20in%201975%2C%20because%20those%20were%20the%20years%20when%20I%20was%20growing%20up.%20I%20had%20just%20entered%20college%20then%20and%20we%20were%20deeply%20conscious%20of%20what%20had%20happened.%20So%20when%20we%20responded%20to%20ADM%20Jabalpur%20and%20overruled%20it%2C%20we%20didn't%20do%20so%20by%20saying%20very%20simple%20words%20that%20there%20was%20a%20constitutional%20error%20or%20there%20was%20a%20legal%20error.%20We%20were%20very%2C%20very%20strong%20about%20it%20because%20you%20feel%20strongly%20about%20an%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandrachud%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20judges%20should%20be%20able%20to%20state%20how%20they%20feel%20about%20an%20issue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20that%20there's%20any%20harm%20in%20a%20judge%20giving%20vent%20to%20how%20strongly%20they%20feel%20about%20the%20issue%2C%20using%20parliamentary%20language...%20It's%20not%20just%20youthful%20angst%2C%20I%20think%20(it%20is)%20constitutional%20angst%20because%20I%20just%20felt%20that%20we%20had%20to%20overrule%20the%20judgment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20stressed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESocial%20Media%2C%20Limited%20Attention%20Spans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20was%20in%20office%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20had%20spoken%20about%20the%20criticism%20of%20judges%20on%20social%20media%20and%20its%20use%20by%20vested%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20whether%20this%20kind%20of%20scrutiny%20made%20a%20judge's%20job%20tougher%2C%20the%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOf%20course.%20Because%2C%20in%20the%20age%20of%20social%20media%2C%20everything%20that%20is%20said%20in%20court%20now%20becomes%20a%20part%20of%20a%20public%20dialogue....%20Now%20every%20little%20word%20which%20is%20said%20by%20the%20court%20or%20by%20a%20judge%20in%20the%20course%20of%20an%20argument%20is%20on%20social%20media%20the%20next%20moment.%20The%20real%20challenge%20is%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20conversation%20which%20takes%20place%20in%20the%20court%20in%20the%20course%20of%20the%20hearing%20of%20a%20case%20does%20not%20reflect%20the%20final%20judgment.%20But%2C%20you%20know%2C%20our%20attention%20spans%20are%20so%20limited%20today%20-%20down%20to%2020%20seconds%20on%20social%20media%20-%20that%20people%20don't%20understand%20the%20distinction%20between%20a%20dialogue%20in%20a%20court%20and%20the%20final%20judgment%20of%20the%20court.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20the%20criticism%20is%20sometimes%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20irrational%26quot%3B%20and%20without%20any%20basis%20in%20concrete%20material%2C%20but%20judges%20have%20to%20face%20the%20new%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BTrue%20To%20Conscience%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandrachud%20said%20he%20spent%20several%20sleepless%20nights%20as%20a%20judge%2C%20thinking%20about%20judgments%20and%20dealing%20with%20administrative%20files.%20He%20shared%20that%20there%20is%20also%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20reflection%20and%20a%20judge%20always%20questions%20himself%2C%20even%20before%20delivering%20a%20judgment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20a%20question%20on%20senior%20lawyer%20and%20Congress%20leader%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%20writing%20in%20a%20newspaper%20that%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20%26quot%3Bwas%2090%25%20right%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20should%20not%20be%20trolled%2C%20the%20former%20judge%20said%20what%20matters%20to%20him%20was%20that%20he%20had%20worked%20to%20the%20best%20of%20his%20ability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20think%20that%20it's%20for%20others%20to%20judge%20my%20work.%20For%20me%2C%20what%20mattered%20was%20that%20I%20was%20true%20to%20my%20conscience%20and%20I%20did%20my%20work%20to%20the%20best%20of%20my%20ability.%20But%20it's%20for%20others%2C%20today%20and%20tomorrow%2C%20to%20assess%20the%20work%2C%20to%20critique%20the%20work%2C%20and%20decide%20whether%20it%20has%20made%20a%20difference%20to%20society.%20For%20me%2C%20it%20was%20(about)%20if%20the%20individual%20cases%20which%20we%20decided%20made%20some%20difference%20to%20society%20-%20%C2%A0whether%20it%20was%2C%20you%20know%2C%20having%20women%20in%20the%20armed%20forces.%20I%20just%20love%20it%20when%20I%20see%20a%20picture%20of%20a%20woman%20fighter%20pilot%20or%20a%20woman%20on%20the%20battlefront%20or%20women%20in%20warships.%20Because%20I%20realised%20that%20has%20been%20transformative%20to%20have%20women%20in%20the%20armed%20forces.%20So%20that's%20the%20degree%20of%20personal%20fulfilment%20which%20you%20have%20as%20a%20judge%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20future%2C%20always%2C%20will%20take%20its%20own%20call.%20Sometimes%20the%20present%20can%20be%20very%20complimentary%2C%20as%20Dr%20Singhvi%20was%20very%20graciously%20complimentary.%20Sometimes%20the%20present%20can%20be%20uncharitable%20as%20well%20to%20judges.%20But%2C%20I%20think%2C%20once%20you%20are%20away%20from%20the%20present%20zone%20of%20conflict%20and%20the%20polarity%20of%20views%2C%20the%20future%20decides%20on%20the%20contribution%20of%20a%20judge%20a%20little%20more%20objectively%20away%20from%20the%20zone%20of%20conflict%20and%20the%20conflict%20of%20ideologies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20stressed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJudicial%20Evasion%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20also%20spoke%20out%20strongly%20against%20charges%20of%20%26quot%3Bjudicial%20evasion%26quot%3B%2C%20saying%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20does%20not%20have%20full%20strength.%20The%20pressure%20of%20work%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20enormous%20and%20picking%20a%20particular%20case%20is%20always%20difficult%20because%20a%20Chief%20Justice%20has%20to%20balance%20constitutional%20issues%20and%20smaller%20cases%20that%20can%20have%20a%20big%20impact%20on%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20uncharitable%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20say%20it%20evades%20cases%20or%20it%20evades%20deciding%20cases.%20The%20court%20has%2034%20judges.%20Today%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20court%20with%20full%20strength.%20Now%20there%20are%20about%2080%2C000%20cases%20which%20are%20pending.%20This%20is%20a%20great%20challenge%20for%20any%20head%20of%20the%20institution%2C%20which%20is%20that%20do%20you%20take%20up%20the%20smaller%20cases%20which%20involve%20a%20big%20impact%20on%20the%20lives%20of%20common%20citizens%20-%20maybe%20a%20civil%20appeal%2C%20a%20criminal%20appeal%2C%20a%20bail%20application%2C%20or%20do%20you%20take%20up%2C%20say%2C%20the%20seminal%20constitutional%20cases%3F%20Because%20when%20five%20or%20seven%20or%20nine%20judges%20are%20assigned%20by%20a%20chief%20justice%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20constitutional%20case%2C%20they%20are%20not%20dealing%20with%20the%20ordinary%20work%20of%20the%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20some%20balance%20has%20to%20be%20drawn%20by%20the%20head%20of%20the%20institution%20on%20how%20many%20judges%20would%20you%20devote%20to%20doing%20the%20normal%20or%20routine%20work%20of%20the%20court%2C%20which%20is%20important%20in%20itself%20because%20you%20are%20dealing%20with%20the%20lives%20of%20individual%20citizens.%20But%2C%20equally%2C%20this%20is%20not%20just%20a%20court%20of%20appeal%2C%20it%20is%20a%20constitutional%20court%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20devote%20sufficient%20resources%20and%20human%20manpower%20to%20dealing%20with%20the%20important%20constitutional%20cases%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandrachud%20said%20that%2C%20in%202024%2C%20close%20to%2060%2C000%20cases%20were%20filed%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20-%20the%20highest%20since%20Independence%20-%20and%20over%2059%2C000%20cases%20were%20disposed%20of%20despite%20Constitution%20benches%20growing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20many%20of%20these%20Constitution%20bench%20cases%20that%20we%20decided%20were%20cases%20which%20were%20pending%20for%20a%20long%2C%20long%20time%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20And%2C%20obviously%2C%20you%20can't%20deal%20with%20all%20of%20them%2C%20but%20I%20tried%20to%20deal%20with%20as%20many%20as%20I%20could.%20But%20I%20don't%20think%20it%20is%20really%20a%20matter%20of%20judicial%20evasion%20when%20a%20case%20cannot%20be%20taken%20up%20by%2C%20a%20court.%20Some%20of%20my%20predecessors%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20if%20they%20couldn't%20take%20up%20a%20particular%20case%2C%20it%20was%20not%20an%20act%20of%20judicial%20evasion.%20It%20was%20just%20because%20of%20the%20pressure%20of%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20only%20when%20you%20are%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20and%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20you%20realise%20the%20enormous%20pressure%20of%20work%2C%20just%20the%20volume%20of%20work%20-%20pressure%20in%20the%20sense%20of%20the%20volume%20of%20work%20which%20you%20have%20to%20handle.%20So%20this%20is%20a%20big%20challenge%20of%20how%20do%20you%20balance%20the%20two%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandrachud%20also%20stressed%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20works%20even%20during%20vacations.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20fact%20that%20the%20first%20victim%20of%20a%20life%20on%20the%20bench%20is%20your%20own%20ability%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20your%20family.%20So%2C%20I%20am%20making%20up%20for%20lost%20ground%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736362200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2F4mhacj58_dy-chandrachud_625x300_08_January_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fndtv-exclusive-dy-chandrachud-judging-can-be-a-lonely-task-ex-chief-justice-dy-chandrachud-to-ndtv-7430233%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Having%20started%20practising%20law%20nearly%2030%20years%20ago%20and%20then%20retiring%20as%20the%20longest-serving%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20in%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20helped%20shape%20jurisprudence%20in%20the%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fndtv-exclusive-dy-chandrachud-judging-can-be-a-lonely-task-ex-chief-justice-dy-chandrachud-to-ndtv-7430233%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NASA%20astronauts%20stuck%2