pUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BCompletely%20Unfounded%26quot%3B%3A%20Ex-Chief%20Justice%20On%20Criticism%20Over%20Court%20Vacations%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20criticism%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20vacations%20is%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20unfounded%26quot%3B%20since%20the%20judges%20are%20working%20%26quot%3B24*7%20and%20365%20days%26quot%3B%2C%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20Dhananjaya%20Y%20Chandrachud%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20exclusive%20interview%20with%20NDTV%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20also%20said%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20is%20among%20the%20world's%20top%20courts%20with%20the%20%26quot%3Blongest%20duration%20of%20working%20days%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BYou%20know%20there%20are%20Supreme%20Courts%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20where%20if%20a%20judge%20sits%20for%20a%20week%20on%20hearing%20cases%2C%20they%20would%20get%20a%20week%20off%20to%20actually%20deliver%20judgment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20over%20the%20top%20court's%20vacations%20has%20cropped%20up%20repeatedly.%20In%202022%2C%20then%20Union%20Law%20Minister%20Kiren%20Rijiju%20told%20Parliament%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20a%20feeling%20among%20people%20of%20India%20that%20the%20long%20vacation%20which%20the%20courts%20obtain%20is%20not%20very%20convenient%20for%20justice-seekers%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20that%20it%20is%20his%20%26quot%3Bobligation%20and%20duty%20to%20convey%20the%20message%20or%20sense%20of%20this%20House%20to%20the%20judiciary%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20whether%20the%20world%2C%20at%20large%2C%20needs%20to%20be%20sensitised%20more%20towards%20the%20vacation%20of%20the%20top%20court%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BAbsolutely.%20I%20completely%20agree%20with%20you.%20For%20the%20reason%20that%20even%20during%20the%20summers%2C%20it's%20a%20partial%20court%20working%20period.%20The%20court%20does%20not%20close%20its%20shutters.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20criticism%20that%20the%20court%20has%20too%20many%20vacations%20is%20completely%20unfounded%20because%20it%20doesn't%2C%20you%20know.%20It's%20not%20justified%20by%20what%20is%20the%20truth%2C%20which%20is%2C%20the%20judges%20are%20working%2024*7%2C%20365%20days.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20CJI%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20victim%20of%20a%20life%20on%20the%20bench%20is%20your%20own%20ability%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20your%20own%20family%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I'm%20making%20up%20for%20lost%20ground%20now%2C%20you%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Chandrachud%2C%20who%20concluded%20his%20tenure%20as%20the%2050th%20CJI%20after%20two%20years%20on%20November%2010%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20written%20reply%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20in%20February%20in%202023%2C%20Mr%20Rijiju%20said%20the%20top%20court%20has%20been%20working%20on%20an%20average%20of%20222%20days%20in%20a%20year.%20He%20said%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Rules%2C%202013%2C%20which%20were%20notified%20in%202014%2C%20provide%20that%20the%20period%20of%20summer%20vacation%20shall%20not%20exceed%20seven%20weeks%20and%20the%20length%20of%20the%20length%20of%20the%20summer%20vacation%20and%20the%20number%20of%20holidays%20for%20the%20court%20shall%20be%20such%20as%20may%20be%20fixed%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20so%20as%20not%20to%20exceed%20103%20days%2C%20excluding%20Sundays%20not%20falling%20in%20the%20vacation%20and%20during%20court%20holidays.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20High%20Courts%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20have%20been%20normally%20working%20for%20210%20days%20in%20a%20year%2C%20according%20to%20a%20statement%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20and%20Justice%20in%202011.%20However%2C%20no%20data%20on%20the%20number%20of%20working%20days%20in%20the%20lower%20courts%20is%20maintained%20centrally%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandrachud%20said%20all%20the%20judges%20of%20the%20top%20court%20work%20throughout%20the%20week%2C%20that%20is%2C%20from%20Monday%20to%20Sunday.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20weekends%20for%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20because%20on%20Saturdays%20and%20Sundays%2C%20you%20are%20doing%20two%20things.%20You%20are%20reading%20for%20the%20Monday's%20cases%2C%2070%20or%2080%20cases%2C%20and%20you%20are%20delivering%20judgments%20which%20have%20been%20held%20back%20in%20reserve%2C%20either%20that%20week%20or%20the%20previous%20week.%20In%20the%20summer%2C%20the%20so-called%20summer%20vacation%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20vacation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%20that%20critical%20constitutional%20cases%20or%20those%20involving%20important%20questions%20of%20law%20are%20mainly%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20dealt%20with%20during%20the%20vacations.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20only%20when%20you%20have%20a%20mini%20break%20or%20a%20longer%20break%2C%20say%2C%20a%20mini%20break%20like%20for%20Holi%20or%20for%20Diwali%20that%20judges%20get%20down%20to%20doing%20all%20this%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOccasionally%2C%20you%20know%2C%20judges%20would%20go%20out%20of%20town.%20But%20even%20when%20they%20go%20out%20of%20town%2C%20say%2C%20on%20a%20Friday%20evening%20and%20come%20back%20on%20Saturday%2C%20they%20are%20addressing%20students%20of%20law%20colleges.%20They%20are%20conducting%20legal%20aid%20camps.%20So%20that's%20equally%20a%20part%20of%20the%20functioning%20of%20a%20contemporary%20judge.%20So%20it's%20not%20that%20judges%20have%2C%20you%20know%2C%20unlimited%20time%20off%20or%2C%20you%20know%2C%20time%20to%20spend%20with%20their%20families%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20several%20judges%2C%20including%20former%20CJI%20N%20V%20Ramana%2C%20have%20said%20that%20there%20is%20a%20misconception%20that%20judges%20stay%20in%20ultimate%20comfort%20and%20enjoy%20their%20holidays.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736354460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fh450nuv8_dy-chandrachud_625x300_08_January_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcompletely-unfounded-ex-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-on-criticisms-over-supreme-court-vacations-7429928%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20criticism%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20vacations%20is%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20unfounded%26quot%3B%20since%20the%20judges%20are%20working%20%26quot%3B24*7%20and%20365%20days%26quot%3B%2C%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20Dhananjaya%20Y%20Chandrachud%20has%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcompletely-unfounded-ex-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-on-criticisms-over-supreme-court-vacations-7429928%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Australia's%20beach%20cabana%20drama%20sparked%20a%20turf%20war%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736353393000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2Fe86b%2Flive%2Fc5d2d7f0-ce11-11ef-87df-d575b9a434a4.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcpw2w8qd7klo%232%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hordes%20of%20shade%20covers%20have%20taken%20over%20Australian%20beaches%20-%20stoking%20debate%20over%20the%20country's%20culture.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcpw2w8qd7klo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcpw2w8qd7klo.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcpw2w8qd7klo.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bisleri%20FY24%20profit%20rises%2082.8%25%20to%20Rs%20317%20crore%2C%20revenue%20at%20Rs%202%2C689.69%20cr%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736353263000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fbisleri-fy24-profit-rises-82-8-to-rs-317-crore-revenue-at-rs-2-689-69-cr-125010801120_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Total%20consolidated%20revenue%20of%20Bisleri%20International%20was%20up%2018.32%20per%20cent%20to%20Rs%202%2C814.04%20crore%20for%20the%20financial%20year%20ended%20on%20March%2031%2C%202024%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ISRO's%20Experiment%20To%20Dock%202%20Satellites%20In%20Space%20Postponed%20For%202nd%20Time%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%20on%20Wednesday%20deferred%20the%20space%20docking%20experiment%20of%20satellites%2C%20for%20a%20second%20time%2C%20citing%20an%20excessive%20drift%20between%20the%20mission%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Space%20Docking%20Experiment%20(SpaDeX)%2C%20was%20originally%20scheduled%20for%20Tuesday.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20later%20postponed%20to%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20X%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20Bengaluru-based%20space%20agency%20announced%20the%20latest%20delay%20but%20did%20not%20provide%20the%20next%20date%20for%20docking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20making%20a%20maneuver%20to%20reach%20225%20m%20between%20satellites%20the%20drift%20was%20found%20to%20be%20more%20than%20expected%2C%20post%20non-visibility%20period.%20The%20planned%20docking%20for%20tomorrow%20is%20postponed.%20Satellites%20are%20safe.%20Stay%20tuned%20for%20updates%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20wrote%20on%20the%20micro-blogging%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20Isro%20had%20deferred%20the%20experiment%2C%20saying%20the%20%26quot%3Bprocess%20requires%20further%20validation%20through%20ground%20simulations%20based%20on%20an%20abort%20scenario%20identified%20today.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SpaDEX%20is%20a%20pivotal%20project%2C%20which%20is%20designed%20to%20develop%20and%20demonstrate%20the%20technology%20needed%20for%20spacecraft%20rendezvous%2C%20docking%2C%20and%20undocking%20using%20two%20small%20satellites%2C%20the%20space%20agency%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSpaDeX%20will%20serve%20as%20a%20milestone%20in%20advancing%20India's%20capabilities%20in%20space%20docking%2C%20a%20critical%20technology%20for%20future%20space%20missions%20including%20satellite%20servicing%2C%20space%20station%20operations%2C%20and%20interplanetary%20missions%2C%26quot%3B%20ISRO%20said%20in%20an%20explainer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2030%2C%20ISRO's%20workhorse%2C%20the%20Polar%20Satellite%20Launch%20Vehicle%20(PSLV)%2C%20lifted%20off%20with%20twin%20220-kg%20satellites%20for%20space%20and%20released%20in%20a%20470-km%20circular%20orbit.%20Docking%20is%20a%20complex%20manoeuvre%20perfected%20only%20by%20China%2C%20the%20US%2C%20and%20Russia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%20involves%20two%20satellites%20separated%20by%2020%20km%20in%20a%20470%20km%20circular%20orbit.%20A%20chaser%20and%20target%20satellite%20move%20at%20a%20speed%20of%2028%2C800%20kmph%2C%20or%2010%20times%20the%20speed%20of%20a%20bullet%2C%20but%20they%20appear%20to%20be%20stationary%20due%20to%20zero%20relative%20velocity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhenever%20the%20docking%20process%20begins%2C%20the%20satellites%20will%20be%20brought%20closer.%20The%20chaser%20will%20approach%20the%20target%20with%20progressively%20reduced%20inter-satellite%20distances%20of%205%20km%2C%201.5%20km%2C%20500%20m%2C%20225%20m%2C%2015%20m%2C%20and%203%20m%2C%20ultimately%20leading%20to%20the%20precise%20docking%20of%20the%20two%20spacecraft.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnWhen%20the%20docking%20takes%20place%2C%20the%20chaser%20will%20move%20closer%20to%20the%20target%20at%20a%20speed%20of%2010%20nm%20per%20second%20and%20hold%20onto%20the%20target.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20ISRO%20chief%20S%20Somanth%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThey%20will%20do%20the%20docking%20exercise%20only%20when%20all%20sensors%20have%20been%20fully%20calibrated%20and%20tested%20to%20satisfaction%20before%20it%20is%20attempted.%20All%20algorithms%20and%20scenarios%20are%20also%20tested%20on%20the%20ground%20before%20commands%20are%20sent%20to%20the%20spacecraft%20to%20autonomously%20do%20the%20docking.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20check%20if%20the%20docking%20is%20successful%2C%20electrical%20power%20will%20be%20transferred%20from%20one%20satellite%20to%20the%20other.%20After%20docking%2C%20the%20satellites%20will%20be%20controlled%20as%20a%20single%20spacecraft.%20The%20process%20will%20be%20declared%20a%20success%20once%20the%20docking%20and%20undocking%20of%20the%20satellites%20is%20done%2C%20after%20which%20the%20satellites%20will%20function%20independently.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736353200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2F374pb04_spadex-_625x300_08_January_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisros-experiment-to-dock-2-satellites-in-space-postponed-for-2nd-time-7429713%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20mission%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Space%20Docking%20Experiment%20(SpaDeX)%2C%20was%20originally%20scheduled%20for%20Tuesday.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20later%20postponed%20to%20Thursday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisros-experiment-to-dock-2-satellites-in-space-postponed-for-2nd-time-7429713%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20slaps%20sanctions%20on%20close%20aide%20to%20Hungary's%20Viktor%20Orban%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736351903000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F1ea3%2Flive%2F414fae00-cdcf-11ef-94cb-5f844ceb