orey-beavis-family-suffers-immeasurable-loss-after-twin-dies-in-thailand-motorbike-crash-13285498%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Maldives%20Attempts%20To%20Rebuild%20Defence%20Ties%20With%20India%208%20Months%20After%20Fallout%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EEight%20months%20after%20New%20Delhi%20was%20made%20to%20withdraw%20its%20military%20personnel%20from%20Maldives%20leading%20to%20frayed%20ties%20between%20the%20south%20Asian%20neighbours%2C%20a%20visit%20by%20the%20Maldivian%20defence%20minister%20to%20New%20Delhi%20aims%20to%20resume%20defence%20cooperaion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDefence%20Minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20on%20Wednesday%20met%20his%20Maldivian%20counterpart%20Mohammed%20Ghassan%20Maumoon%20in%20New%20Delhi%20for%20high-level%20talks%2C%20including%20on%20boosting%20the%20defence%20preparedness%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20archipelago.%20During%20the%20meeting%20Mr%20Singh%20conveyed%20India's%20readiness%20to%20enhance%20defence%20ties%20with%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20press%20statement%2C%20the%20bilateral%20talks%20between%20the%20two%20leaders%20were%20wide-ranging%2C%20but%20revolved%20around%20the%20core%20resolve%20to%20work%20closely%20in%20realising%20the%20joint%20vision%20for%20India-Maldives%20comprehensive%20economic%20and%20maritime%20security%20partnership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20stated%20that%20the%20two%20ministers%20reviewed%20in%20all%20aspects%20of%20bilateral%20defence%20and%20security%20cooperation%20in%20great%20detail.%20%26quot%3BDuring%20the%20talks%2C%20both%20sides%20reasserted%20the%20firm%20commitment%20to%20work%20closely%20in%20realising%20the%20joint%20vision%20for%20India-Maldives%20Comprehensive%20Economic%20and%20Maritime%20Security%20Partnership%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Defence%20Ministry%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajnath%20Singh%20underscored%20India's%20willingness%20to%20support%20Maldives%20in%20enhancing%20its%20defence%20capabilities.%20He%20also%20conveyed%20India's%20readiness%20to%20provide%20defence%20platforms%20and%20military%20assets%20to%20augment%20Maldives'%20security%20preparedness.%20Mr%20Singh%20reiterated%20New%20Delhi's%20'Neighbourhood%20First'%20policy%20and%20its%20vision%20for%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EREBUILDING%20AFTER%20A%20STORM%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20months%20Maldives%20has%20tried%20to%20mend%20ties%20with%20India%2C%20which%20took%20a%20damaging%20hit%20after%20its%20current%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20adopted%20an%20anti-India%2C%20pro-China%20stance%20after%20his%20electoral%20win.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20Male%20risked%20harming%20a%20centuries-old%20cultural%20relationship%20and%20decades-old%20bilateral%20ties%20it%20had%20with%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20day%20after%20his%20victory%20in%20the%20presidential%20election%2C%20Mr%20Muizzu%20declared%20that%20it%20wants%20India%20to%20withdraw%20all%20its%20military%20personnel%20present%20in%20Maldives%20for%20civil%20assistance.%20He%20declared%20that%20Maldives%20will%20maintain%20autonomous%20control%20over%20all%20its%20territories%2C%20including%20maritime%2C%20aerial%2C%20and%20terrestrial%20domains%20apart%20from%20enhancing%20Maldives'%20capabilities%20for%20conducting%20underwater%20surveys.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%202024%2C%20he%20had%20said%20that%20the%20first%20group%20of%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20will%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20New%20Delhi%20before%20March%2010%2C%202024%2C%20and%20ordered%20the%20remaining%20personnel%2C%20manning%20two%20aviation%20platforms%2C%20to%20be%20withdrawn%20before%20May%2010%20the%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%2088%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20were%20in%20the%20Maldives%20primarily%20to%20operate%20two%20helicopters%20and%20an%20aircraft%20that%20have%20carried%20out%20hundreds%20of%20medical%20evacuations%20and%20humanitarian%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReports%20suggest%20that%20Maldives%20was%20willing%20to%20take%20China's%20help%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20Maldives%20had%20on%20January%2023%2C%202024%20permitted%20China's%20Xiang%20Yang%20Hong%2003%2C%20a%20vessel%20equipped%20to%20carry%20research%20and%20surveys%2C%20to%20dock%20at%20Male%20port%2C%20saying%20the%20halt%20was%20for%20replenishment%20and%20that%20the%20research%20vessel%20would%20not%20be%20conducting%20any%20research%20while%20in%20the%20Maldivian%20waters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Muizzu%20had%20also%20broken%20tradition%20by%20opting%20not%20to%20make%20New%20Delhi%20his%20first%20port%20of%20call%20after%20assuming%20office.%20In%20fact%2C%20his%20first%20visit%20to%20New%20Delhi%20came%20as%20recently%20as%20October%202024%20-%20nearly%20than%20a%20year%20after%20he%20became%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20President's%20visit%20three%20months%20ago%2C%20ties%20between%20Maldives%20and%20India%2C%20which%20had%20broken%20down%20severely%2C%20are%20seeing%20an%20effort%20to%20be%20rebuilt%20with%20visits%20from%20both%20the%20foreign%20minister%20and%20the%20defence%20minister.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736342400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2F1kks26u4_rajnath-singh-maldives-defence-minister-mohammed-ghassan-maumoon-ani_625x300_08_January_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmaldives-attempts-to-rebuild-defence-ties-with-india-8-months-after-fallout-7428598%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Eight%20months%20after%20New%20Delhi%20was%20made%20to%20withdraw%20its%20military%20personnel%20from%20Maldives%20leading%20to%20frayed%20ties%20between%20the%20south%20Asian%20neighbours%2C%20a%20visit%20by%20the%20Maldivian%20defence%20minister%20to%20New%20Delhi%20aims%20to%20resume%20defence%20cooperaion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmaldives-attempts-to-rebuild-